Synonym of cocky, used several times in the book Adam Bede. “...couldn't abide a fellow who thought he made himself fine by being coxy to's betters..." or "...You may talk o' these things for hours on end, and you'll only be all the more coxy and conceited for't..." or "...he sits an' shakes his head, an' looks as sour an' as coxy when we're a-singin' as I should like to fetch him a rap across the jowl..."